Author: Sebastian Utz <su@rtme.net>
Date:   Mon Feb 3 16:54:15 2025 +0100

    Fix SubQueryResults.merge(), result values of both sides must be used
    
    When merging 2 SubQueryResults, the result values of both sides
    must be taken into account and merged.
    
    Fixes #17307.
    
    (cherry picked from commit 5e1bc6c9d8ed874baa4fc99500561c4e94c37d9d)

diff --git a/docs/appendices/release-notes/5.9.10.rst b/docs/appendices/release-notes/5.9.10.rst
index 62951bf921..2615538801 100644
--- a/docs/appendices/release-notes/5.9.10.rst
+++ b/docs/appendices/release-notes/5.9.10.rst
@@ -65,3 +65,16 @@ Fixes
         ) u
     ORDER BY name
 
+- Fixed an issue that caused an error when using a correlated sub-query and
+  a normal subquery on the same level together with an additional sub-query on
+  an outer level. Example::
+
+    WITH tbl AS (SELECT 1 as x)
+    SELECT (
+      SELECT x FROM tbl
+      WHERE t.x = tbl.x
+        AND tbl.x IN (SELECT x FROM unnest([1]))
+    ),
+    (SELECT y FROM unnest([2]) as t2(y))
+    FROM tbl t
+
